<SECOND>PM-Bakker Sentence-Glance,0223</SECOND>
<HEAD>Bakker Sentencing At a Glance</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Bakker Sentence, Bjt</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here, at a glance, are details of the sentence given Jim Bakker,
founder of the PTL television ministry:
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   PRISON SENTENCE: 45 years.
   PAROLE POSSIBLE: After 10 years.
   FINE: $500,000.
   CHARGES: Eight counts mail fraud, 15 counts wire fraud and one
count conspiracy to commit mail and wire fraud.
   MAXIMUM POSSIBLE SENTENCE: 120 years.
   TRIAL: Nearly six weeks long, more than 100 prosecution witness,
75 defense witnesses.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   Here is a breakdown on the prison sentence:
   Counts 1 and 2, mail fraud, 5 years.
   Counts 3 and 4, mail fraud, 5 years.
   Counts 5 and 6, mail fraud, 5 years.
   Counts 7 and 8, mail fraud, 5 years.
   Counts 9, 10, 11, wire fraud by telephone, 5 years.
   Counts 12, 13, 14, wire fraud by television, 5 years.
   Counts 15, 16, 17, wire fraud by television, 5 years.
   Counts 18, 19, 20, 21, 22, 23, wire fraud by television, 5 years.
   Count 24, conspiracy to commit mail and wire fraud, 5 years.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   Here is a breakdown on the fine:
   Count 2, mail fraud, $100,000.
   Count 3, mail fraud, $200,000.
   Count 24, conspiracy, $200,000.
</TEXT>
