<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--EasternArrests     10-25 0156</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Eastern Arrests,0158</SECOND>
<HEAD>Eight Airline Employees Arrested in Airport Theft</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Eight Eastern Airlines employees
were arrested on charges of stealing things such as drugs and
jewelry at Palm Beach International Airport, authorities said.
   U.S. Attorney Dexter Lehtinen announced the indictment Tuesday
against 15 Eastern employees on charges such as conspiracy to steal
from the U.S. mail, theft from the U.S. mail and conspiracy to
steal credit cards.
   The charges resulted from a one-year investigation into the
theft of Express Mail aboard Eastern Airlines aircraft. According
to the indictment, the employees were instructed by a
co-conspirator on how to take the contents from Express Mail
envelopes.
   One Express Mail shipment contained 14 spools of 25-foot and
50-foot lengths of gold chains. Officials said the conspirators
split the proceeds when the chains were sold. Several defendants
were charged with removing marijuana and cocaine from the mail and
distributing it to others.
</TEXT>
