<HEAD>Zsa Zsa Trial Video Due Next Week</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Zsa Zsa Sentencing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   You've seen her on TV. You've read about her
trial in newspapers. Next week, the video: ``The People vs. Zsa Zsa
Gabor.''
   The videotape of Miss Gabor's trial for slapping a Beverly Hills
policeman goes on sale nationwide Oct. 31, said Jay Lebow, director
of development for TriCoast International, the producer.
   The 60-minute tape chronicles the Hungarian-born actress's trial
from jury selection to her sentencing to 72 hours in jail Tuesday.
It goes for $9.95.
   More than 500 copies have already been sold in advance to
retailers, Lebow said. ``The interest has been incredible,'' he
said. ``We've only been selling it for a few days.''
   Lebow said the trial was ``real-life `Dynasty,''' and that the
people who'll rent or buy it will be ``people who read `People,'
people who read the `National Enquirer''' and lawyers ``who have an
interest in how the court system is exploited.''
   TriCoast acquired the footage from the one camera allowed inside
the courtroom and the rest from a local video production company.
   ``The video isn't biased,'' Lebow said. `` But I think that most
of the people were against her. They thought that she was caught in
an unfortunate situation then turned it into a media blitz for
herself.''
