<FIRST>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     10-25 0523</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0540</SECOND>
<HEAD>For Much of the Nation, It's Indian Summer</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Sunny, warm conditions lingered in much of the nation today.
   Indian summer prevailed across the central third of the country
Tuesday as brisk southerly winds helped temperatures warm into the
70s and 80s across the Great Plains and the Mississippi Valley.
   Readings of 80 degrees were reported as far north as southern
Minnesota and southeastern North Dakota.
   Fifteen cities in the north-central United States tied or broke
the record highs for the date, including a high of 74 in
International Falls, Minn., dubbed ``The Nation's Icebox'' because
of its bitterly cold winters.
   Al Voelker, a National Weather Service spokesman in Fargo, N.D.,
where the mercury climbed to a record 78, said goose hunters might
be disappointed because the heat might prevent geese from flying
low enough to hunt, adding:
   ``It seems a lot hotter than what it is. When you get used to
40-degree weather, it seems hotter.''
   The warm weather spread to the East with highs mostly in the 60s
and 70s, though temperatures remained in the 50s in parts of Maine.
   Showers and thunderstorms were scattered across the Florida
Peninsula as well as southern Texas. Rain lingered in southwestern
Oregon and northern California, with snow in the highest
elevations. Half-inch hail was reported with a thunderstorm at Red
Bluff, Calif.
   Clouds and scattered showers prevailed behind a cold front
crossing the northern Plains. Clouds covered much of the nation
west of the Rockies.
   Temperatures warmed into the 80s and low 90s in the desert
Southwest. Cool, blustery weather prevailed across much of the rest
of the West.
   The nation's high on Tuesday was 92 degrees at Borrego Springs,
Calif.
   Readings at 2 a.m. EDT today:
   _East: Atlanta 54 fair; Boston 50 fair; Charleston, S.C. 57
fair; Chattanooga 45 fair; Cincinnati 53 fair; Cleveland 52 fair;
Detroit 49 foggy; Hatteras 63 fair; Jacksonville 56 fair; Key West
72 fair; Knoxville 45 fair; Macon 41 fair; Miami 68 partly cloudy;
New York 48 fair; Philadelphia 45 fair; Pittsburgh 48 foggy;
Portland 39 fair; Richmond 45 fair; Tampa 65 fair; Washington, D.C.
45 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 41 fair; Chicago 60 fair; Denver 48 fair; Des
Moines 61 fair; Indianapolis 55 fair; Kansas City 67 fair; Little
Rock 59 foggy; Louisville 54 foggy; Memphis 60 fair; Nashville 52
fair; New Orleans 52 fair; North Platte 58 fair; Oklahoma City 63
fair; Omaha 64 fair; Rapid City 54 fair; St. Louis 67 partly
cloudy; Minneapolis-St. Paul 58 fair; Sault Ste. Marie 47 foggy;
San Antonio 68 partly cloudy.
   _West: Anchorage 27 cloudy; Boise 46 cloudy; Casper 49 partly
cloudy; Fairbanks 18 snow; Great Falls 42 fair; Honolulu 77 partly
cloudy; Las Vegas 66 windy; Los Angeles 64 windy; Medford 42 fair;
Pendleton 45 fair; Phoenix 72 partly cloudy; Portland, 51 cloudy;
Reno 39 showers; Salt Lake City 62 partly cloudy; San Diego 66
partly cloudy; San Francisco 55 fair; Seattle 50 partly cloudy;
Spokane 34 fair.
   _International: Montreal 45 fair; Ottawa 46 fair; Regina 43
partly cloudy; Toronto 45 foggy; Winnipeg 54 fair; Mexico City 52
fair; Acapulco 77 thundershowers.
