<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--NightStalker-Rewards     10-25 0157</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Night Stalker-Rewards,0160</SECOND>
<HEAD>$36,777 in Rewards OK'd in Night Stalker Case</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) Nineteen people who played roles in the capture
and conviction of Richard Ramirez in the so-called Night Stalker
case will get $36,777 in rewards from Los Angeles County.
   The top reward of $10,388 goes to Jesse N. Perez, who provided
authorities with Ramirez's name and facts about the crimes and
helped recover a murder weapon.
   Other rewards range from $250 to $1,000 for providing
information to various authorities, helping capture Ramirez in East
Los Angeles or directing police to Ramirez on the day of his arrest.
   The money will be awarded at a yet-to-be-scheduled ceremony,
county supervisors said in deciding the awards Tuesday.
   Ramirez was sentenced to death after he was convicted on 12
counts of first-degree murder, one count of second-degree murder
and 30 other felonies stemming from a string of nocturnal attacks,
most of them in the summer of 1985.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
