<DOCNO> AP891025-0235 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-10-25-89 0208EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f PM-BusinessHighlights     10-25 0773</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Business Highlights,0808</SECOND>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The jitters that triggered the stock market
plunge on Friday the 13th crept back into financial markets,
causing wide price swings in stocks, depressing the dollar and
boosting demand for U.S. Treasury bonds.
   Speculation that a collapsed deal to buy United Airlines parent
UAL Corp. signaled a continued ebbing of the takeover tide that has
helped boost stock prices, and that a slowing economy would mean
weaker corporate profits, helped set the tone for the market
gyrations Tuesday, analysts said.
