<TEXT>
   Yields on 2-year Treasury notes fell at
auction to the lowest level since April 1988.
   The average yield Tuesday was 7.74 percent, down from 8.39
percent at the last comparable auction on Sept. 26.
   It was the lowest rate since 2-year notes averaged 7.64 percent
on April 27, 1988. The notes will carry a coupon interest rate of
7| percent with each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,979.10.
   A total of $10.04 billion in notes were sold out of bids
totaling $24.17 billion.
