<FIRST>u f PM-CineplexOdeon     10-25 0324</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Cineplex Odeon,0337</SECOND>
<HEAD>Cineplex Chairman Planning Bid for Company</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TORONTO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Cineplex Odeon Corp. Chairman Garth Drabinsky is
planning a bid worth $666.8 million to buy his company, the firm
said today.
   Drabinsky and his long-time partner, Myron Gottlieb, are trying
to arrange financing for a $14 per share cash offer, Cineplex said.
   Cineplex's biggest shareholder, Los Angeles-based entertainment
giant MCA Inc., has agreed to sell its stake _ worth $330 million
under the proposed bid _ if Drabinsky can arrange financing and
mail the offer by Nov. 22, Cineplex said in a statement.
   The other big shareholder, Claridge Inc. of Montreal led by
Charles Bronfman, has also agreed to tender its $94.7 million stake
under the same conditions, Cineplex said.
   Cineplex owns more than 1,800 screens in about 500 locations in
North America. Drabinsky founded the chain a decade ago.
   A special committee of the Cineplex board would continue to meet
with other interested bidders until the Drabinsky offer is firm,
company spokesman Brian Hemming said.
   Cineplex stock was down 37{ cents to $10.87{ a share in early
New York Stock Exchange trading today.
   Drabinsky's proposed bid is less than the nearly $15 a share he
originally offered to buy out the Claridge stake and gain control
of the company piecemeal several months ago.
   MCA had objected to that move and regulators quickly quashed the
bid, saying Drabinsky was required to make the same offer to all
shareholders.
   Under their agreement with Drabinsky, MCA and Claridge retain
the right to pull out of any deal with him and tender their shares
to a higher competing bid, Cineplex said.
   The Cineplex statement also said MCA and Claridge have agreed to
buy the Universal City 18-screen complex in Los Angeles and lease
the facility back to Cineplex if the Drabinsky bid goes through.
   Cineplex also said it would sell its 51 percent stake in Film
House to joint-owner Rank Organization PLC of Britain.
</TEXT>
