<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-SaraLee     10-25 0204</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Sara Lee,0210</SECOND>
<HEAD>Reports Record Earnings for First Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sara Lee Corp. reported record first-quarter
earnings Wednesday, a 24.1 percent increase over the year-ago
period.
   Earnings for the three months ending Sept. 30, the company's
first fiscal quarter, rose to $93.8 million from $75.6 million for
the same period last year, the Sara Lee said in a statement.
   Earnings per share increased 15.4 percent to 75 cents, compared
with 65 cents a year ago. The lower percentage increase in earnings
per share is due to a higher level of preferred dividends and more
common shares outstanding in the current quarter, the Chicago-based
company said.
   Quarterly sales totaled $2.7 billion, down 0.1 percent from last
year's level, due to the disposition of Sara Lee's food service
business at the beginning of their 1990 first quarter.
   ``Earnings growth remained strong during the quarter,'' said
John E. Bryan, chairman and chief executive officer. ``In spite of
restructuring our foodservice business which resulted in an annual
loss of more than $1 billion in sales, our core operations reported
solid results, with outstanding performance in our personal
products businesses.''
   Sara Lee makes and sells packaged food and consumer products
such as printed T-shirts and hosiery.
</TEXT>
