<HEAD>Du Pont Earnings Up 19 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WILMINGTON, Del. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Du Pont Co. reported Wednesday that it's
third-quarter profit jumped 19 percent over a year ago despite a
stronger dollar and weaker housing market.
   The chemical giant said that net income for the three months
ended Sept. 30 totaled $547 million, or $2.36 a share, compared
with earnings of $461 millin, or $1.91 a share, the same time last
year.
   Sales rose 9 percent to $8.6 billion from $7.9 billion.
   ``We are pleased with third quarter results, which were achieved
despite a stronger dollar and a weaker housing market,'' Du Pont
Chairman Edgar S. Woolard Jr. said in a statement.
   ``Most businesses in our portfolio continue to out perform
prior-year levels ... We expect 1989 to be our fourth consecutive
year of increased earnings.''
   For the first nine months of this year, Du Pont's profit rose 18
percent to $1.9 billion, or $8.46 a share, from $1.6 billion, or
$7.03 a share, in 1988.
   Sales were up 10 percent to $26.5 billion from $24.1 billion.
