regulations so that dangerous chemicals can be taken off the market
more quickly, sources say.
   Environmental Protection Agency Administrator William K. Reilly
declined on Wednesday to provide details of the impending policy
announcement, but told reporters ``it's responsive to a number of
problems this agency has had in administering our pesticide law.''
